The best way to get from Kinshasa to the airport is by taxi. Alternatively, you can take a bus, which costs $1 - $2 and takes 1h 30m.

Want to know more about travelling around Democratic Republic of the Congo

Democratic Republic of the Congo, also known as DR Congo, DRC, DROC, Congo-Kinshasa, or simply the Congo, is a country located in Central Africa. It is sometimes anachronistically referred to by its former name of Zaire, which was its official name between 1971 and 1997. - Wikipedia

The National Museum of Kinshasa (French: Musée National de Kinshasa) is a museum in Kinshasa, Democratic Republic of the Congo. It is located in the city centre, in the district of Limete, on the Avenue de la Liberté.

The National Museum of Kinshasa (French: Musée National de Kinshasa) is a museum in Kinshasa, Democratic Republic of the Congo. It is located in the city centre, in the district of Limete, on the Avenue de la Liberté. The museum was founded in 1960 and is the largest museum in the country.
